BorgWarner’s Roger Wood to Become Dana’s CEO, WSJ Reports

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-03-30T04:29:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/borgwarner-s-roger-wood-to-become-dana-s-ceo-wsj-reports.html
BorgWarner Inc. (BWA)  veteran Roger Wood
is to be named the new chief executive officer of Dana Holdings
Inc., replacing chairman and interim CEO John Devine, who is
retiring, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing Dana.  Devine, who is leaving the company, will be replaced as
chairman by Keith Waddell, chief executive officer of Harley-
Davidson Inc., the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Chris Peterson  at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  